Practical No. 6: Configure IOS Intrusion Prevention System (IPS) using CLI

Aim

Configure IOS Intrusion Prevention System (IPS) using CLI:
(a) Enable IPS
(b) Modify an IPS signature

Steps

Step 1: Verify Connectivity

Configure IP addresses on PCs and router interfaces.

Test connectivity using ping.

PC> ping 192.168.1.1

Step 2: Enable IPS on Router

Router> enable
Router# configure terminal
Router(config)# ip ips notify SDEE
Router(config)# ip ips name MY_IPS_LIST
Router(config)# interface g0/0
Router(config-if)# ip ips MY_IPS_LIST in

Step 3: Modify IPS Signature

Router(config)# ip ips signature-definition MY_SIG
Router(config-ips)# signature 1001 action drop
Router(config-ips)# exit
Router(config)# interface g0/0
Router(config-if)# ip ips MY_IPS_LIST in

Step 4: Verify IPS

Router# show ip ips config
Router# show ip ips statistics
Router# show running-config